items.title: Dacelo novaeguineae
items.content_text: This is an example of nature at its cruelest.  The little bird got too wet when bathing, was attempting to get safe on the platform provided and was taken by the Kookaburra.  It is the first time I have lost a bird at my watering ponds (that I know of).

items.title: Accipiter fasciatus
items.content_text: Need help with the ID - two stills and the video show many angles.

items.title: Daphoenositta chrysoptera
items.content_text: There were two and it appeared as though they were gathering nesting material.  Then one returned to the same tree to search for food.

items.title: Anthochaera carunculata, Grallina cyanoleuca
items.content_text: First time I have seen the Magpie-lark in our garden.  There were actually two of them but only one shows in the upper left hand corner of the video.

items.title: Myiagra cyanoleuca
